communications.subject: Washington Public Records Act Request: PDR Logs 2023-2024
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Washington Public Records Act, I hereby request the following records:

Public disclosure request log (log of public records requests received by your agency, along with request description/summary, classification, date of receipt, date closed/resolved, time dedicated to processing each request, current status, final resolution, etc.) of records requests sent to your agency since January 1, 2023.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 5 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Rose Terse

communications.subject: Washington Public Records Act Request: Discovered Apps
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Washington Public Records Act, I hereby request the following records:

The aggregate list of discovered apps on City-owned devices enrolled in Microsoft Intune mobile device management in CSV format. You can find instructions on how to export this list here:
https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/mem/intune/apps/app-discovered-apps#monitor-discovered-apps-with-intune

Please select "Export the discovered apps raw data set" when asked.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 5 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Rose Terse
